This paper deals with natural language processing and distributional semantics, which are typically associated with the computer science subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also uses machine learning techniques to learn vector-based composition models, which falls under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of these models for relation classification and sentence completion, which are tasks commonly associated with artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions the use of structured queries, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper discusses the use of vector-based models for image captioning, which is a task commonly associated with computer vision (cs.CV).
